04.05.2025 Italy 🇮🇹
Torino supporters made a march in the city centre to protest against the owner. Around 20k people participated, with also representations of Genoa ultras and supporters from Fiorentina, River Plate, Benfica.
Yesterday it was also the commemoration of Superga tragedy of 1949, when Grande Torino died in the airplane accident. Every year in 4th may supporters and the entire team (players, staff and the OWNER) go to Superga to commemorate them. Yesterday, for the first time, the owner Urbano Cairo was obliged to not go with the team for security reasons, he had to go alone in the morning, while 20k fans were protesting against him in the city centre.

30.04.2025 Netherlands 🇳🇱
Well known Brigata Tifosi (De Graafschap) from the Netherlands are disbanding by their own choice.
After 21.5 years, we have decided with a heavy heart to stop as BT. A decision that has been coming for some time, but which we have been able to postpone through various efforts in recent years. Unfortunately, there are a number of factors, both inside and outside the group, that make it impossible to continue supporting our club as we have done for all those years. And so we have to be honest, to ourselves and to the club. We do it with full dedication, or we don't do it at all. This is the reason why we have made the decision to put an end to BT after this season. Of course, this does not mean that we will no longer be seen at De Spinnekop or during away matches. A fanatic Graafschapper is something you are for life!

Marseille vs Brest. ultras Marseille (South Winners group) made a tribute to the Pope.

In 2023, the Argentine Pope Francis visited Marseille’s Vélodrome Stadium and famously declared, « I come to Marseille, not to France »This rebellious statement displeased the Parisian elites but strongly resonated with the people of Marseille, who share proud rebellious values rooted in the Mediterranean and Argentine values that is closeness to the people over allegiance to the elites. This phrase was later honored yesterday night by the South Winners 87 Ultras , a group deeply inspired by the revolutionary Argentine Che Guevara, to pay tribute to Pope Francis.

12.04.2025 Austria 🇦🇹
Grazer AK with choreography in a home match against Altach

The figure you see is Dionysus, the god of wine in Greek mythology, who represents freedom and celebration.
A glass of wine in one hand, a football in the other, and a cigar in his mouth.

He is wearing a shirt with the club’s emblem, on which it says “20 years.”
At the center of the shirt, it says RED FIRM – the name of the club’s ultra group, which is celebrating 20 years.
(The Red Front).

On the banner below the figure it says: “Dionysus loves us.”
And in the third image it says: “And we love the red.”

The fourth and final image – another choreography from the same match.
A design that mimics an ancient Greek-Roman wall painting, with mythological scenes.

At the center of the choreography is the club’s emblem,
and the year it was founded: 1902.
Notice the wine jug, on which the founding year of the club – 1902 – is also engraved.
